member.example:
This example demonstrates how to use with LINQ method syntax. ClassWithFields is a custom class with a public field called Text. The Select method returns a FieldInfo instance representing the Text field.
FieldInfo fi = new Fields<ClassWithFields>().Select(v => v.Text);
This example demonstrates how to use with LINQ query syntax. ClassWithFields is a custom class with a public field called Text. The Select method returns a FieldInfo instance representing the Text field.
FieldInfo fi = from v in new Fields<ClassWithFields>() select v.Text;

